Source: secubox-smtp-relay
Section: mail
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Gerald KERMA <devel@cybermind.fr>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://cybermind.fr/secubox
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: secubox-smtp-relay
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, secubox-core (>= 1.0), postfix | msmtp
Recommends: libsasl2-modules, ca-certificates
Description: SecuBox SMTP Relay — Email forwarding through smarthost
 SMTP relay module for SecuBox that configures outbound email forwarding
 through a smarthost (upstream SMTP server).
 .
 Features:
  - Smarthost configuration with SASL authentication
  - TLS encryption support (mandatory TLS or opportunistic)
  - Mail queue management (view, flush, delete)
  - Delivery statistics and real-time log viewing
  - P31 Phosphor light theme web interface
 .
 Port Debian bookworm de luci-app-smtp-relay (SecuBox OpenWrt / CyberMind.fr).
